Road
width_and_accuracy
 value in mm
 accuracy %
#detection envelope -> EventEnvelope
#inclination_and_curvature->InclinationAndCurvature

Road.InclinationAndCurvature
# we already have things like Vehicle.AngularVelocity.Pitch,Yaw but obviously can differ - indicating maybe not all wheels are on the road
# file:///home/edwardguild/doc/covesa/fleet/sensoris-specification-v1.6.0-public/doc/index.html#sensoris.protobuf.types.base.Int64ValueAndAccuracy
longitudinal_inclination_and_accuracy # Longitudinal declination and accuracy, also referred as slope. (degrees)
lateral_inclination_and_accuracy # Lateral declination and accuracy, also referred as cross fall. (degrees)
horizontal_curvature_and_accuracy # Horizontal curvature and accuracy. Negative value represents curve to the left, positive value represents curve to the right. Value of 0 represents straight road. The value is the reciproke of the radius (curvature = 1/radius) whereas high radii are represented by low values.

