Road.RoadAttribution.Lane

#EventEnvelope
# relative_lane_id int64: Relative lane identifier. Identifier is 0 for ego-lane, +1 for lane directly left of vehicle, +2 for lane left of lane +1, -1 for lane directly right of vehicle, -2 for lane right of lane -1.
width_and_accuracy mm and %
InclinationAndCurvature - which Road already has - do we need both? obviously can be different between lanes

Road.RoadAttribution.Lane.LaneBoundary.

EventEnvelope
lane_boundary_id Lane boundary identifier. Identifier is unique within a DataMessage and can be used to trace lane boundaries between LaneBoundary events.
existence_confidence
